scenario:
The local loop pointer 'pos' is declared as a pointer to a non-const type although it is only used for read access (inspecting fields like pos->kind, pos->header_size, pos->value_size, pos->header, pos->value and following pos->next). According to MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 it should point to a const-qualified type when possible. Change the declaration to:

const struct MHD_HTTP_Req_Header *pos;

This preserves existing assignments from a non-const headers list and enforces immutability of the referenced objects within this function.
